It’s been hard to put words and emotions into text on a screen… Our dear friend Marcio, how sad I am for your family and for all of your friends you left behind. You were a true shining light, always smiling, always stoked, always syked on the surf whether it was knee high or 60ft Pe’ahi. I have so many fond memories of surf sessions with you and it makes me giggle thinking of some of our fish market days. You and Yuri and Danilo showed us it was possible and are why we are all living our dreams paddle surfing at Pe’ahi. So sad to see you go, but I know your light shines on through all of us that you touched. Thank you so much for your friendship, until we meet again, see you later 🙏 Nothing but love for you 💜💜💜@marciofreiremaddog

What a wild few days 🤯… still processing it all and honestly, I think it may take a bit. It started off on a high, with this wave being my highlight of the #marcioswell 🌊 That swell was gifted by Marcio for sure, we all felt his presence. From the perfect giant waves to the huge pod of dolphins guiding us in to #peahi as we arrived. What a memorable swell, so amazing to see #jaws do her thing again 🙏 I’ve been eyeing a wave like this for a while… a few mistakes and a bit too big of a board, but the vision was insane and I know what I need to do next time to make a wave like this #🐬🦅 
Thank you for the clip #redbullmagnitude I look forward to the next opportunity to back door one of these beauties 🙏🤙🙏

Very excited for tomorrows @theeddieaikau event at Waimea Bay ⚡️⚡️⚡️ It’s a dream come true to surf alongside the long list of competitors, all of which inspire me in their own unique ways 🌊 The first time I ever got to paddle out for the Eddie ceremony, I must have been 12 or 13, staying with @xococoho and @cocom4debarrelkilla and Uncle Mike brought us to the bay for the paddle out. Never in my wildest dreams as a kid did I think I’d one day be in the #eddieaikauinvitational 💜 and even getting to surf both of my heats with Uncle Mike 🙌. I am humbled, honored, fired up!!! and extremely proud to represent Maui as one of 6 female invitees and 34 men. The first time the event has run that the women will surf alongside the guys! It is going to be an amazing day celebrating Eddie’s legacy, big wave surfing, and the amazing camaraderie of ocean athletes.  Link in my bio to watch live on @surfline . Let’s go!!!!! #thebaycallstheday
📷 @sweetwaterhawaii @seanordonez

Magical experience at the #eddieaikauinvitational yesterday. I’m still processing the whole day, it was a wild experience with a lot of energy and a LOT of people!!! So grateful to be a part of this event, thank you so much to the @theeddieaikau Aikau family for the invitation. It means the world to me 🙏More to come… 
📷 @chachfiles

Still processing the whole experience of the #eddieaikauinvitational 🙌 There were so many moments that will live on in my memories of this historical event. From the amount of people in the bay and all the energy tightly held together in Waimea Valley… the word MAGIC comes to mind ✨✨✨ The #eddieswell was by far the most consistent #bigwave swell I’ve ever been a part of. Sets were 5 minutes apart for the entire day with a lot of them closing out the entire bay at #waimea. What an incredible swell and it was sunny and offshore all day 🙌 The #watersafety teams did some of the best A+++ driving ever, thank you 🙏 The crowd cheering for us as we walked down the beach was one of the coolest experiences ever and really got us fired up to go out and push it! To all of the people behind the scenes for putting on event with such little notice, it truly was a community event, thank you @theeddieaikau for the invite 💜 Being a part of this event was not only a dream come true, but one of the biggest honors of my life. This event was so much bigger than words do justice… so there’s still more to come. 🙏🙏🙏
📷 @traviskeahi

The thing about a first time, is it only happens once. This year, 6 women surfed alongside 34 guys in the Eddie… for the very FIRST time in 37 years!!! I believe it’s something to celebrate 🎉 A huge moment in surfing and in sport and I’m so so so excited that this was the start of a huge change  and I had the privilege of being a part of it all. It was a spectacular day and I had so much fun surfing alongside the men that were supportive of the women (you know who you are, thank you 🙏) It’s not easy putting on an event like this, thank you so so much to the Aikau Foundation, the event staff, the water safety, and everyone involved that made this day so special. I’m grateful that this first time happened, so now when @izzigomez_ @annie__starr @skylar_lickle @zoechaitsurfs and others coming up compete in this event in the future that they won’t have to ask “what about the women?” Or “what were the scores”. I cannot believe we didn’t get a photo of all of us together (and I can’t believe I didn’t get one with my mom!) It was a pretty chaotic energy filled day that I’m still soaking in. Grateful to be in the mix and honored to be involved, and I know Eddie would be very proud of all the women who showed up and sent it! I’ve had hundreds of messages asking how the women did… well, this was my best wave… and the highest score of the women. No it wasn’t the biggest best wave like I wanted to catch, but I was proud to successfully ride this thing til the bitter end of the whitewash before gracefully belly flopping out of it 😆 This was my first session at big Waimea (or ever depending on your version of big, since I was 16). Hard to leave Pe’ahi when it’s good, same swells as Waimea. I could use more time learning the lineup, but my takeaway is I’m proud of riding 3 successful rides to the channel and one good wipeout too 😂 And I’m really proud to be one of the 6 ladies that were a part of this event. 🙏  Thank you so much @pedrogomesphotography for sharing this 🎥

This winter I’ve found myself reminding my younger friends, that big wave surfing is a life long pursuit… 🤓🤔 you don’t always get everything you want in one session or one winter. And even when it’s a firing winter 🔥 and you do get that “one” or have an incredible day, you are still on the hunt for more 🤷‍♀️ Surfing is never settled, you can always improve, always get a better one, always be deeper (or wider)… and it’s rare that everything aligns 🤞 That is why certain waves are more memorable than others and give you that soul filling stamp in the memory bank 💫 This wave, I’ve been searching, for a few years now… and damn I wish I was 30 ft wider (sorry Ian 🤪) and riding one of my shorter boards (like I have been all winter 🤦‍♀️) But I’ve looked at this wave, all different angles (thank you 🎥 @guy__mac for sharing this with me, really appreciate it 🤙) and know exactly what I need to do next time the opportunity arises. So for now, it is memorable in the sense that it’s the “one that got away” and the hunt continues. 
I really hope winter isn’t over 🙏
#marcioswell #theonethatgotaway #peahi #jaws #redbullmagnitude

I think this is one of my favorite photos in a very long time 🫶. Waves have been my passion for such a long time, but the past few years I’ve found a connection with soil that fills my soul in the same way the ocean has. I guess that connection has always been there but I’ve tapped in more deeply when putting roots into my own property. I always find it funny when I type soil and my auto correct wants it to be soul. This is a beautiful citrus orchard at a friends place surrounded with comfrey and perennial peanut feeding the soil all around the trees. Heaven! This to me, is similar to rocking up at a perfect barreling wave with no one around but you and your best friends. Exactly what I envision our lil farm to be like, Thriving!! It’s been amazing to spend a few days hanging with my dear friends @leahloves @surfchica6 @chelsea_kinch . Definitely needed this time in nature, good laughs, sisterhood and bde 😆 sure love my friends 💜 Filling my soul in all the ways this weekend 🙌 #ariesseason♈️

Well, I finally took up the SUP foil thing ⚡️I’ve been tentative for a long time as I was just never really into stand up paddling. This summer being flatter than flat here on Maui, it was time for a change and a challenge 🤪 Winging saved me the past few summers, but after a while, I found down winding just wasn’t as exciting anymore and only really wanted to wing in waves 🌊 Summer projects at our little farm took precedence and I wasn’t in the water as much as I’d liked… I was getting grumpy and knew I needed more water time…🤯 My amazing group of friends (of all ages, talents, genders) have all been egging me on for a while to try the sup thing. I decided it was finally time to give it a go! 😁I borrowed too small of a board and completely suffered… could barely stand on the thing and tallied up my first three short runs into one, as they literally did not count. @sos_shapes had been making a few new boards for @liftfoils so I had him make me something more stable and the first run was a significant improvement and the second day I had gotten 50% better 💪 Day three was definitely a breakthrough and I had multiple glides of a few minutes. Everyday I’d come in and text @gordito_surfs the update on the tiny breakthroughs. Felt like he was there every run encouraging me to keep trying and I wanted him to feel like he was with us! Every good glide I thought “This is what Casey was talking about! Do it for Casey!!!” 💜 I think I’m on 10 or 11 now. I’m obsessed. I’m grateful for the ability to get on the water everyday riding waves (that mostly don’t break) and sharing the stoke with my friends. The reason I fell in love with foiling was escaping the surf crowds and enjoying a mushy crap wave with just a few happy friends. 😁The stoke is real. The freedom of being out at sea is incredible. Navigating the thoughts in my mind has been really interesting. You’re so present that riding the bumps becomes intuitive and so many thoughts come flying from all over the place. Absolutely loving this new challenge!!! ⚡️⚡️⚡️
7-8 100lt and 150 HAX 26carve

I’ve found it hard to sit down and write a post here, while my time and efforts could be better used for boots on the ground efforts. I’m at a loss for words and my heart hurts 💔 These fires on Maui have been horrific, words do no justice what has happened here on the west side and upcountry. My heart aches for those that lost loved ones and for the whole town of Lahaina, who’s lives have been completely changed.  These photos are of Lahaina, which holds such a special place in my heart for so many reasons, but at the top of that list are the people. People make community. Through this tragic devastation, I have seen the most beautiful outpour of unity in community here on Maui. Immediate help came from the Maui community and everyone I know has been doing what they can to help. From our first responders and to the unspoken hero’s who did unthinkable actions amidst the fires and after, thank you. Thank you to all of the volunteers throughout the whole island doing everything from housing people, delivering medical needs, supplying and collecting goods, being leaders in the community people can depend on. Thank you to those cooking for thousands and the people doing gas, solar, water deliveries… Thank you to those creating fundraisers, the outer island boat deliveries being unloaded by skis to get items to shore, the camps being set up to get supplies out, keiki initiatives, the list is endless… Thank you to the people helping spread the message to help donations being sent from around the world… If you have the means, please donate directly to families impacted or organizations helping people directly, this is going to be a long process and the people will need our help 🙏 
Maui is strong. Please allow the West side space to grieve, but please don’t forget about the rest of the island. Our island is hurting island wide and in order for people to continue giving to those in need, everyone needs support. Support local businesses. Support local farmers. Support your neighbors. Spread love 🙏#mauistrong

We planted this tree 3 years and 1 month ago 🌴 It was probably a year old at the time and begging to to get out of the pot she was in… Our dear pup Mocha passed away months prior and @coconutinformation gifted us this tree in her memory 🙏 We decided to spread some of her ashes amongst the roots, knowing that as the tree grew, we’d always see her from our bedroom windows and she would be right next to us 🥹 Mocha has been thriving since she got in the ground. Our pups lay beneath her shade and get to chew on some of her cocos and it fills our hearts so much 🫶🫶🫶 We got our first drinkable cocos this week and the smiles it brought drinking our first one, brought Sean and I to tears. We thought “maybe in 5 years if we’re lucky” but it only took 3. No fertilizer. No BS. Just good old regenerative practices, it’s amazing what nature can do when we work together. So very grateful, thank you Mocha baby!! 🫶🫶🫶 @hydroflask #myhydro #hydroflask #ambassador

Been wanting to put up a post of some fun stuff we’ve been doing in the gym 💪 @deep2peak (thank you always 🙏) definitely bringing the heat 🔥 during these chilly 🥶few days at home! Working on some springy stuff this week 🔝💪 As I went to write this, I had a moment thinking about my sister Tanya. When I was little, she was really fit, and I always told her I was going to be taller than her one day 😜 I remember her telling me a story of when she was walking home from work one evening and she got jumped by a guy and she was able to fend him off of her “because she was strong” Sadly these stories are all too familiar nowadays. I always thought it was cool to be strong because my sister was (and my mom, who was always running and swimming)… I am so grateful that my body can do so many amazing things and I plan to take care of it so that I can continue doing fun shit into my 80s/90s or maybe even 100 like my grandfather 🤷‍♀️. I’m grateful for the ability to use it to its utmost potential. I’m grateful I was taught from a young age that it’s “cool to be strong” because yes it makes you paddle faster!! 💪 I hope at least one kid sees this and thinks “I wanna do that!” Because really, what’s the point of these videos if not to help inspire the next generation (or even you 🫵) to get after it 🔥🔥🔥
#getafterit #workoutdaily #heartrateup #workout #fitnessmotivation #deep2peak

Passing on smiles with purpose.

When we asked our ambassador squad on Maui @mattmeola @paigealms and @Torreymeister (legends) how we can help support the community’s healing after the catastrophic wildfires, they all brought meaningful ideas and were already passionately taking action. Through their guidance we teamed up with an incredible organization @boards4buddiess to bring surfboards shaped by @ajwsurfboards and @sanuk sandals to some folks affected by the fires. 

@Boards4Buddies provides surfboards and skateboards to deserving kids in underserved communities. These boards provide a positive outlet for kids to improve mental health, as well as to nurture a diverse and supportive community. A worthy cause if you ask us. Check them out!

Thank you to everyone involved for helping us support community healing through the joy of surfing. 🌺💚👍
